com.okta.sdk.impl.ds.cache

Interface ResourceCacheStrategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultResourceCacheStrategy

    public interface ResourceCacheStrategy
    Defines the strategy used for reading/adding/updating/removing objects from the cache based on a ResourceDataRequest and ResourceDataResult.
    Since:
    1.0

      • readFromCache

        ResourceDataResult readFromCache(ResourceDataRequest request)
        Attempts to retrieve data from the cache based on the request. If the object is NOT found in the cache, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        request - the source request used to query the cache.
        Returns:
        A result containing data from cache, or null
